comment: LATR shows that Gortat (WAS) cleanly blocks DeRozan's (TOR) layup attempt. Any body to body contact after the block is incidental.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Carroll (TOR) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RATR shows that Beal (WAS) loses control of the ball on his own while Joseph (TOR) maintains legal guarding position.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Joseph (TOR) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Biyombo (TOR) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Sessions (WAS) after the shot has been released.
Porter (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as DeRozan (TOR) slips during his drive.
Biyombo (TOR) sets the screen on Wall (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LHH shows that Lowry (TOR) and Carroll (TOR) cleanly strip the ball from Gortat (WAS).
Biyombo (TOR) commits a take foul on Sessions (WAS).
Carroll (TOR) commits a take foul on Wall (WAS).
Gortat (WAS) makes contact with DeRozan's (TOR) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Lowry (TOR) commits a take foul on Wall (WAS).
Sessions (WAS) maintains legal guarding position and does not affect DeRozan's (TOR) RSBQ on the drive.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Joseph (TOR) released his 3 point field goal prior to the clock expiring was upheld.
